com.qubulus.qps
Class DummyPositioningService

java.lang.Object
  Service
      com.qubulus.qps.AbstractPositioningService
          com.qubulus.qps.DummyPositioningService

public class DummyPositioningService
extends AbstractPositioningService

A dummy implementation of a positioning service, meant to be used during development or for demo purposes. The position estimate returned is one of the two hardcoded values, alternating at each request.

Configuration

The following mock geocoordinates should be provided as Android string resources, describing two positions that the service will consecutively return:

  • dummy_map0
  • dummy_lat0
  • dummy_lon0
  • dummy_map1
  • dummy_lat1
  • dummy_lon1
If the map and/or the latitude and/or the longitude or a position is missing, the position returned will be unknown.

An optional latency (in ms), to simulate sensor and/or network is configurable via:

  • dummy_delay

Permissions required

  • android.permission.WAKE_LOCK
